<!-- ===== THE GAP ===== -->
<section id="story">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="kicker">The Honest Problem</div>
    <h2>Cattle Country That Can't Buy Its Own Beef</h2>
    <div class="rule"></div>
    <p class="lead big">We sit in the heart of cattle country, yet the best beef raised here gets shipped a thousand miles away, processed by strangers, and trucked back as a commodity box on a grocery shelf. The families who raise America's finest cattle can't easily buy good, local beef back.</p>
    <p class="lead" style="margin-top:26px;">So folks default to cheaper proteins — not because they want to, but because real, traceable, locally-raised beef was never on the menu. <strong class="gold">We're here to put it back.</strong></p>
  </div>
</section>

