    <div class="kicker">From Pasture to Freezer</div>
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <div class="rule"></div>
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="num">1</div>
        <h3>Pick Your Animal</h3>
        <p>Choose your animal from local Sandhills herds — the kind you can drive out and see standing in the grass. Buy a quarter, a half, or the whole.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="num">2</div>
        <h3>We Harvest &amp; Dry-Age</h3>
        <p>Your animal is harvested fresh — before it ever touches a commodity truck — then carefully dry-aged for flavor and tenderness, the way good beef should be.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="num">3</div>
        <h3>Fill Your Freezer</h3>
        <p>Cut, wrapped, and ready to feed your family for months — at a better price per pound than the meat counter, especially on the premium cuts.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="lead" style="margin-top:48px;font-size:19px;color:#c7c0b1;">Because you own the animal, it's processed for you and your family — fresh, honest, and yours.</p>
  </div>
</section>

